oai_dc:dc.dc:title: East Side of Joseph Avenue Alley, c.1950s
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph of homes along the east side of the Joseph Avenue alley, between Foster and Marks Streets in East Nashville, c.1950s. The area was part of the East Nashville Urban Renewal Project (Project Tenn. R-13). Photographed by Jerry Hiland of the Nashville Housing Authority. Forms part of the MDHA Photograph Collection. 1 photograph : b & w.
